{"id":"decision-trending-cursor-stability","type":"decision","fact":"Trending sort cursor pagination uses created_at as the stable keyset key instead of the computed time-decay score, because the score shifts every second and would produce incorrect pagination.","recommendation":"For trending feed pagination, ORDER BY the computed score but use created_at+id for the WHERE clause in cursor-based keyset pagination. Accept slight ordering drift between pages.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"Issue #17 design spec — security review + spec review","date":"2026-04-12"}],"tags":["pagination","cursor","trending","feed","postgresql"],"affectedFiles":["packages/server/src/db/queries/feed.ts"],"affectedServices":["findFeedPosts"],"createdAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-12T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
